# Test Project

## Description

This project uses Express.js for the backend, Webpack for frontend bundling, and Jest for testing.

## Installation

To install all dependencies, run the following command:

```bash
npm install
```

## Running the Project

To run the project in production mode, use the following command:

```bash
npm start
```

## Running in Development Mode

To run the project in development mode, use the following command:

```bash
npm run dev
```

This script runs two processes concurrently using concurrently:
Webpack — serves the frontend in development mode.
Nodemon — automatically restarts the server when backend files change.

## Building the Project

To build the project for production, use the following command:

```bash
npm run build
```

This script builds the project using Webpack in production mode.

## Testing

To run tests using Jest, execute the following command:

```bash
npm test
```

This script runs Jest to test your code.

## Technologies

Express.js — for the backend.

Webpack — for bundling and serving the frontend.

Jest — for testing.

Concurrently — for running multiple processes simultaneously in development mode.

Nodemon — for automatically restarting the server during development.